textBeforeTable: Items Checked Out by Month The Technology and Support Services section of the Library provides technical support to staff and public computers, assists in the checking in and out of books, manages the book catalog database, and maintains the agency’s website. Although Technology and Support Services staff does not offer programs directly to our patrons, staff had been extremely busy at the Circulation Desk during the summer months. What is your library worth to you? How much would you pay out-of-pocket for your library services? Enter in the left hand column the number of times per month you or your family use each service. Estimated retail value of each service (if purchased) will be calculated on the right. Total value of your library use is shown at the bottom of the worksheet. Tip: Tab between entries and do not use commas.
